I did however clear out most censorship from the dataset. Most can be erased simply by using another LoRa or by using 'censored' in your negative prompts. It does typically do it's best at removing it on its own though.

Generally speaking the ckpt you use shouldn't really matter, obviously it's dependent on how censored it is and filters and the like, I've been using yesmix for the duration of the creation of this mode, but I've found others can have interesting effects, AOMnsfw generated much more realistic lighting effects for example. This LoRa is very diverse in my opinion, but extremely detailed prompts or prompts in specific positions, as well as those containing lots of characters in one go can screw it over (since not every cg in Milk Factory games is a head on shot it can generate a lot of weird extra booba) and you might get floating boobs with legs or something crazy like that. So keep it clear and concise, and try to combine LoRa's and play around with weighting to receive a better result <3
